commentable_entity.title: California state courts: Amber Heard Brought to Justice
commentable_entity.description:
Amber Heards false accusations of Johnny Depp in 2017 has caused a serious impact to the iconic actors career.

Johnny lost a role he loved "Captain Jack Sparrow" and has since been deemed uncastable by many large production companies. He went from an A-Tier actor to be defamed and humiliated by Heard and the #Metoo campaign.

It is not just this that seems Amber Heard should face justice infront of a judge. Amber is the embodiment of how women view abuse to men today. She needs to be an example that abuse is not accepted no matter your Gender. And that lying about it makes it only worse.

In this as well I want to demand the return of Johnny to his A-List Roster. The apology of judges who presided over the case. And apology of large production companies who turned their backs on him such as Disney. Johnny suffered through abuse leading to mental illness resulting in a downhill spiral from 2015-2019 and the results of that should be repaid by Amber HeardÂ

Johnny lost a role he loved "Captain Jack Sparrow" and has since been deemed uncastable by many large production companies. He went from an A-Tier actor to be defamed and humiliated by Heard and the #Metoo campaign.

It is not just this that seems Amber Heard should face justice infront of a judge. Amber is the embodiment of how women view abuse to men today. She needs to be an example that abuse is not accepted no matter your Gender. And that lying about it makes it only worse.

In this as well I want to demand the return of Johnny to his A-List Roster. The apology of judges who presided over the case. And apology of large production companies who turned their backs on him such as Disney. Johnny suffered through abuse leading to mental illness resulting in a downhill spiral from 2015-2019 and the results of that should be repaid by Amber HeardÂ

I had the Samsung happen to me, a 1st Sgt, 28 year reservist, Verizon worker for 27 years, And after the charges were dropped I still was treated like a enemy of the state.
Living in Mexico.
